{
  "texts": [
    "For example, most humans spoke about retirement.",
    "However, the LLM did not do so even though it was possible to infer retirement from other elements of the backstories such as age and co-morbid conditions.",
    "The Forward continuity is partially satisfied, while silicon participants did not produce surprising responses that are inconsistent with the explicit prompt, they did not infer additional barriers and enablers that make sense for their backstory, for example, rapid change in physical activity levels since retirement, which was mentioned by humans without prompting.",
    "Algorithmic fidelity describes the ability of a large language model (LLM) to accurately reflect the ideas, beliefs, and attitudes situated in sociocultural contexts of various population groups [4].",
    "We introduce a method for checking the algorithmic fidelity of an LLM's textual responses through framework-based qualitative research."
  ]
}